cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with attacking video recognition models. It may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a heuristic-based algorithm to measure the importance of each frame in the video towards generating the adversarial examples. Additionally, it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as it deals with videos. It may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as it proposes a method to generate adversarial examples. Finally, it may belong to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category as it deals with adversarial attacks.
